name: Fairview Aircraft Restoration Society PBY-5A Canso Takeoff from Red Deer Airport
description:
Please take a look at the Fairview Aircraft Restoration Society's website and consider making a donation to keep this magnificent aircraft flying: www.savethecanso.com

This PBY-5A Canso, a Canadian-built version of the PBY Catalina, a flying boat used during World War II, paid Red Deer a visit on Sunday May 27th for the "Props and Pistons" event held by YQF. In the days leading up to the event, I heard that this unique bird was going to be there, and needless to say, I wanted to catch it! Here we have Canso FNJE starting up, taxiing, and departing Red Deer Regional Airport on runway 17 for its home base in Fairview, Alberta, some 500 kilometers northwest of Red Deer. This is certainly one of the more unique aircraft that I've filmed, hope you enjoy this special catch!

Thanks for watching!

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

FLIGHT INFORMATION
Aircraft: Canadian Vickers PBY-5A Canso
Livery: Buffalo Airways 
Engines: 2x Pratt & Whitney R-1830-92
Registration: C-FNJE
Route: Red Deer Regional (YQF) - Fairview (CEB5)
Callsign: Foxtrot November Juliet Echo
Runway used: 17
Date filmed: May 27, 2018
Local time: 1700
